teresting features. From the West Gate to the oross street Venella, the space was covered by the Manor House and grounds, possibly the abode of Hugh de Venele in the reign of Henry the Third. Several centuries later, a large Mansion was erected on the spot by one of the Lockyers’, then become the wealthiest and most influential family in Ivelchester. A portion of this edifice, comprising the two Eastern gables‚ was taken down many years ago: the remainder was converted into the Manor Farm House.
